{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5949a97b-1892-47ec-98aa-4724f9256c86","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. Here's what matters:\n\n**Framework support dropped in MSTest v3:**\n- **`netcoreapp3.1`** — ❌ Not supported. MSTest v3 requires **.NET 6.0+** for .NET Core targets.\n- **`net5.0`** — ❌ Not supported. .NET 5 is out of support; MSTest v3 requires at least .NET 6.0.\n- **`net462`** — ✅ Still supported (.NET Framework 4.6.2+).\n\nYou'll need to update your `TargetFrameworks` to something like `net6.0;net462` (or `net8.0;net462`) before upgrading.\n\n**Package changes in MSTest v3:**\nThe separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages are consolidated into a single **`MSTest`** meta-package.\n\n**To migrate**, you'd update the csproj roughly like:\n\n```xml\n<TargetFrameworks>net8.0;net462</TargetFrameworks>\n...\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.x.x\" />\n```\n\nWould you like me to apply these changes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"bb166c79-8055-4cc2-a276-9b074cf5107e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The project targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. The user wants to migrate from MSTest v2 (2.2.10) to MSTest v3.\n\nKey compatibility issues with MSTest v3:\n\n1. **Dropped framework support**: MSTest v3 drops support for older target frameworks. Specifically:\n   - `.NET 5.0` is no longer supported (it's out of support from Microsoft anyway)\n   - `.NET Core 3.1` is no longer supported\n   - `.NET Framework 4.6.2` — MSTest v3 requires at least .NET Framework 4.6.2, so `net462` should still be supported. Actually, let me think more carefully. MSTest v3 supports .NET Framework 4.6.2+, so `net462` should be fine.\n   \n   Actually, reconsidering the minimum supported frameworks for MSTest v3: it requires .NET Framework 4.6.2+ and .NET 6.0+ for .NET Core/.NET. So `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` both need to be upgraded to at least `net6.0`, while `net462` remains compatible.\n\n2. **Package consolidation**: In MSTest v3, the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages are consolidated into a single package.\n\n3. **Breaking changes**: There are various API and attribute changes to account for.\n\nLet me clarify the compatibility issues for you.","outputTokens":722,"requestId":"7C20:203FDB:2C43471:3138C1E:69F95A74"},"id":"fe24a3a2-fb0b-4036-93dc-7ef45a885910","timestamp":"2026-05-05T02:48:33.597Z","parentId":"ca83a785-1fec-45b8-be97-012f40152586"}
